properties.description: Posted by Baobot2575 Glen Helen Pkwy., San Bernardino, CA, United States Hyundai Pavilion at Glen Helen is the nation\'s largest amphitheater, with the capacity to accommodate over 65,000 people. Located where the 15 and 215 freeways meet in Devore, the Pavilion hosts some of Southern California\'s biggest concert events. Situated within the Glen Helen Regional Park, the venues beautiful natural setting readily lends itself to concerts and festivals. The concert season runs from April through October and has featured such artists as Brooks and Dunn, Sammy Hagar, Tom Petty, CHER, Eminem, Aerosmith, ZZTop, KISS as well as special events like the World\'s famous Ozzfest and the KROQ Inland Invasion. The state of the art sound system and venue lay-out lead to the ideal concert experience. We welcome you to enjoy a season of world-class music at the Hyundai Pavilion at Glen Helen. ---www.hyundaipavilion.com

properties.name: Renee Fisher
properties.description: Posted by IvoteforthecureHello Everyone... I\'m a proud 28 year old,mother of 2, married for ten years, breast cancer patient. I began my journey on August 3, 2007. I\'m pleased to report I have finished chemo and I\'m on to bigger and better things. The face of breast cancer is changing, it\'s no longer a middle aged womans disease and I\'m elated to say I VOTE FOR THE CURE!!!! God Bless You All. ~Renee~

properties.description: Posted by Deisnor Anchorage, AK, USAPlatial Nearby lets you see more of the world around you.
